body:
<!--
Thank you for filing a bug report! 🐛 Please provide a short summary of the bug,
along with any information you feel relevant to replicating the bug.
-->

I tried this code:

```sh
./x.py check
```

I expected to see this happen:
Rust's compilation check complete successfully.

Instead, this happened:
```
error: failed to get `ar` as a dependency of package `rustc_codegen_cranelift v0.1.0 (/Users/dantebroggi/Documents/GitHub/rust-test/compiler/rustc_codegen_cranelift)`

Caused by:
  failed to load source for dependency `ar`

Caused by:
  Unable to update https://github.com/bjorn3/rust-ar.git?branch=do_not_remove_cg_clif_ranlib#de9ab0e5

Caused by:
  failed to map 'auto'; class=Config (7)
command did not execute successfully: "/Users/dantebroggi/Documents/GitHub/rust-test/build/x86_64-apple-darwin/stage0/bin/cargo" "check" "--target" "x86_64-apple-darwin" "-Zbinary-dep-depinfo" "-j" "8" "--release" "--manifest-path" "/Users/dantebroggi/Documents/GitHub/rust-test/compiler/rustc_codegen_cranelift/Cargo.toml" "--message-format" "json-render-diagnostics"
expected success, got: exit code: 101
failed to run: /Users/dantebroggi/Documents/GitHub/rust-test/build/bootstrap/debug/bootstrap check
Build completed unsuccessfully in 0:00:04
```
